					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of probably of the end of 13th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>201 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>268</height>
										<width>203</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="lines">
										<height>24</height>
										<width>1</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>201 folios (+ 4 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end of the codex).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Originally 28 or more quires, mostly of 10 leaves each, marked clearly by a catchword and in Pentateuch also by a Hebrew letter. Seven quires are missing at the beginning, one quire after folio 30, and one after folio 70.</p>
									<p>Several leaves are missing after folio 127 and at the end of the manuscript.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Several folios mutilated.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="24" writtenLines="24">
									<p>Pricking and ruling with a hard-point on hair side are visible. </p>
									<p>Wide margin was left ruled for masoretic notes.</p>
									<p>Writing is suspended fron the upper margin.</p>
									<p>Pericopes are only marked by the first word written in larger letters. פתוחות וסתומות clearly observed.</p>
									<p>Very rare masoretic notes (see folio 20v).</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
